Updating proposed CDDL to reflect convention that we disallow multiple instances of the same type measurement.

```
reference-endorsed-triple-record = [
  environment-map ; identifies the target environment
  ref-map ; reference measurements that match evidence
  end-map ; endorsements that are accepted if above reference values match evidence
]
 
ref-map = {
  &(ref-vals :0) =>  measurement-map / measurement-values-map ; no time series data as reference values is possible
}
 
end-map = {
  &(end-vals :0) => [ + measurement-map / measurement-values-map ] ; array denotes time series data – array index 0 is the most recent value, index n is most historical value
}
```
Note: the use of ref-map and end-map may be pedestrian, but helps to illustrate the part handles time series and the part that handles conditional endorsement.

Option (b) sounds fine. With issue #2 incorporated, will the triple definitions be something like below?

```
$$triples-map-extension //= (
  comid.reference-endorsed-triples => [ + reference-endorsed-triple-record ]
)
comid.reference-endorsed-triples = 7

reference-endorsed-triple-record = [
  environment-map ; identifies the target environment
  [ + reference-endorsed-measurement-map ] ; reference values with endorsed values
]

reference-endorsed-measurement-map = {
  &(mval: 1) => [ + measurement-values-map ] ; If multiple array entries exist then apply series comparison semantics
  ? &(authorized-by: 2) => [ + $crypto-key-type-choice ]
}

reference-endorsed-measurement-map = {
  &(ref-vals :0) => [ +  measurement-values-map ]
  &(end-vals :1) => [ + measurement-values-map ]
}
```

